description:
Job Highlights:

Accurately place customer orders and shop replenishment within the specified time
Managing stock levels and transferring stock between locations
Coordinate all logistics operation including warehouse, retail locations and transportation
Handle inventory control to keep stock record
Prepare various report for operation review
Perform ad-hoc duties as required

Requirements:

F.5/HKDSE or above
1-2 years relevant working experience in retail industry;
Good computer skills: Microsoft Word and Excel, Chinese word processing;
Experience with ERP/WMS system is preferable, knowledge of  “縱橫系統” Dynamic System will be an advantage ;
Strong sense of responsibility and able to work independently;
Ability to perform multi-task, well-organized, self -motivated, efficient, detail-minded and able to work under pressure;
Immediate availability is preferred

 Interested candidates please send application with full resume, availability and expected salary.

Accompanying the company development, we are looking for you, the outstanding candidate for:-

Administration Assistant


The post is to assist the administration officer in:-

Verifying and dispatching of daily customer purchase orders;
Preparing tender document in high accuracy level;
Maintaining office supplies, office equipment and environment;
Handling incoming calls and greeting visitors in a professional and courteous manner when necessary;
Communicating with internal department for administrative issues;
Any other administration tasks as assigned by supervisor and assist the team in ad-hoc  projects
Contract-based, annual contract renewal is expected

To excel in this role, you will need to have the following requirements:

Diploma graduate or above in related discipline.  
Minimum 1 year sales administration and / or office administration experience;
Responsible, detail oriented, independent, well-organized and good team player
Proficient in MS Word, Excel
Immediately available is preferable

Interested candidates, please send your resume, with present and expected salary to us.

 Getinge Group Hong Kong | Internet: www.getingegroup.com

Responsibilities:

Provide full range administration support, including order input, delivery arrangement and invoice preparation in Oracle system.
Work closely with internal and external customer for daily work of purchasing and business control.
Prepare the monthly report.
Handle ad hoc projects as assigned.

Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above with 4 years' relevant working experiences;
Experience and knowledge in Oracle System is an advantage;
Excellent communication and inter-personal skills;
Good command of both written and spoken of Chinese and English;
Immediate available is preferable.
Please send your full detailed resume with expected salary and date available to The Human Resources Manager, NEC Hong Kong Limited, 25th Floor, The Metropolis Tower, 10 Metropolis Drive, Hunghom, Kowloon or by e-mail.


Personal data provided by job applicant will be used strictly in accordance with employer's personal data policy, a copy of which will be provided immediately upon request.

Accompanying the company development, we are looking for you, the outstanding candidate for:-

Assistant, Service Administration (Contract-based)


Responsibilities:-

SAP system input for service call creation and confirmation;
To prepare  sales / service-related documents includes quotation...etc, in high standard of data accuracy;
Coordinate and liaise closely with service team, to ensure timely information delivery and case follow-up;
Working with customer for their asset maintenance system update;
Any other administration task as assigned by supervisor, assist the team for ad-hoc projects

Job requirements:

High diploma / Sub-degree holder, service admin related experience is preferred;
Working experience in medical equipment / healthcare market will be a strong advantage;
Experience in SAP system is preferred;
Responsible, able to prioritize, good team player and in good discipline;
Able to communicate in Chinese and English (writing)

This job is a long term contract based and contract is supposed to be renewed yearly with gratuity.
Interested candidates, please send your resume, with present and expected salary to us.

 Getinge Group Hong Kong | Internet: www.getingegroup.com

We are looking for a high caliber candidate to develop his/her career in our Company：

The Job :

To handle customers' enquiries, orders and complaints in an efficient and professional manner;
To manage parts order processing, and monitor backlog status and parts delivery;
To follow up with customers for invoicing and payment arrangement;
To analyze GM% and freight cost of sales orders so as to improve the profitability;
To liaise with central service team for pricing and lead time checking;
To act as key user for Internal Service Program and solve the issues raised by service technicians (training will be provided);
To drive and grow parts sales by actively contacting customers and identifying their needs;
To support the service jobs schedule and maintenance service team;
To provide feedback on the efficiency of customer service process;
Ad-hoc projects assigned by line Manager.

The Person:

Degree in Business Administration or equivalent;
Min. 2 years relevant experience in customer service or sales administration. Proven track record in order processing；
Independent, fast learner, self-motivated, details-minded, well organized and able to work under pressure;
Business acumen and Customer-oriented;
Good interpersonal and negotiation skills;
Good command of spoken and written English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Knowledge in SAP will be an advantage;
Fresh graduate will also be considered.

We offer competitive remuneration package and generous fringe benefits including 5-days work week, medical and dental insurance, discretionary bonus and excellent working condition. Interested candidates please apply through JobsDB.

All information received will be kept in strict confidence and only for employment-related purpose.

Requirements:

University graduate in business discipline or equivalent;
At least 3-5 years related working experience in sales administration duties,  IT & Retail industry is preferable;
Good communication and interpersonal skills;
Good command in both English and Chinese writing.

We offer a competitive remuneration package to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your full resume with present and expected salary by email to recruitment®karin.com.hk or clicking 'Apply Now'.

(We are an Equal Opportunity Employer and personal data collected would be used for recruitment purpose only.)
